{"timestamp":"2026-03-18T13:46:00.156Z","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","session_id":"7ce0d5b2-2369-474e-aa53-1f5c4f234574","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/7ce0d5b2-2369-474e-aa53-1f5c4f234574.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: Production Deployment to Ubuntu 24.04 + Caddy + PostgreSQL\n\n## TL;DR\nAdd a `deploy/` directory to the repo with 4 deployment artifacts and extend the Makefile with 4 new targets. After a one-time server setup (5 short steps), every future deployment is a single `make deploy` command.\n\n## Context / Findings\n- **Backend routes** (must proxy to Go binary at `localhost:8080`):\n  - `/auth/*` — OAuth login, callback, logout, me, token\n  - `/user/*` — URL CRUD endpoints\n  - `/r/*` — short-URL redirect (`/r/{shortcode}`)\n- **Frontend** — Vue 3 SPA built by Vite; all other paths served as static files with SPA fallback\n- **Prod env loading** — reads OS env vars ONLY (no `.env` files); managed via systemd `EnvironmentFile`\n- **DB migrations** — manual in prod (`sql/schema.sql` for initial setup, numbered files for incremental)\n- **No existing** deploy scripts, systemd units, or Caddyfile\n- **`.gitignore`** needs `bin/` added\n- **Target arch**: Linux amd64 (same as dev machine → no cross-compilation issue, but use explicit GOOS setting for safety)\n- **`APP_BASE_URL`** is also the frontend's API base URL — must be set at Vite build time\n\n---\n\n## Phase 0: Add deployment artifacts to the repo\n\n### 1. `deploy/linkshortener.service` (systemd unit)\n- Runs as `linkshortener` system user from `/opt/linkshortener`\n- Loads all env vars from `EnvironmentFile=/etc/linkshortener/environment`\n- `Restart=on-failure`, `RestartSec=5s`\n- Security hardening: `NoNewPrivileges=yes`, `PrivateTmp=yes`, `ProtectSystem=strict`, `ReadWritePaths=/opt/linkshortener`\n\n### 2. `deploy/Caddyfile` (template with placeholder domain)\n- `your.domain.com { ... }` — user replaces domain before copying to server\n- Caddy auto-TLS via Let's Encrypt (requires ports 80/443 open)\n- `handle /auth/*`, `handle /user/*`, `handle /r/*` → `reverse_proxy localhost:8080`\n- Catch-all `handle` → serve `/opt/linkshortener/frontend` with `try_files {path} /index.html` + `file_server` (SPA mode)\n- `encode zstd gzip`\n\n### 3. `deploy/environment.template`\n- All vars from `ai-instructions/app-environment.md` with placeholder values\n- `LINKSHORTENER_ENV=prod` pre-filled (not a secret)\n- Secrets marked `CHANGE_ME` with generation hints (e.g., `openssl rand -hex 32`)\n\n### 4. `deploy/server-setup.sh` (idempotent one-time setup script)\n- Creates `linkshortener` system user (skip if exists)\n- Creates `/opt/linkshortener/frontend/` + `/etc/linkshortener/`\n- Sets ownership to `linkshortener`\n- Copies `environment.template` → `/etc/linkshortener/environment` (chmod 640, root:linkshortener) — only if file doesn't exist yet (preserves existing secrets on re-run)\n- Installs + enables `linkshortener.service` systemd unit\n- Prints \"NEXT STEPS\" instructions at the end\n\n### 5. Makefile additions\n```\nbuild-backend-prod:\n    mkdir -p bin\n    cd backend && CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o ../bin/server .\n\nbuild-frontend-prod:\n    cd frontend && LINKSHORTENER_ENV=prod APP_BASE_URL=$(APP_BASE_URL) npm run build\n\nbuild-prod: build-backend-prod build-frontend-prod\n\ndeploy: build-prod\n    rsync -avz bin/server $(SSH_HOST):/opt/linkshortener/server\n    rsync -avz --delete frontend/dist/ $(SSH_HOST):/opt/linkshortener/frontend/\n    ssh $(SSH_HOST) \"sudo systemctl restart linkshortener\"\n```\n- Also add `bin/` to `.gitignore`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: One-time server setup (5 steps)\n\n**Step 1 — Create PostgreSQL database + user** (run on server via SSH):\n```bash\nsudo -u postgres psql -c \"CREATE USER linkshortener WITH PASSWORD 'strong-password';\"\nsudo -u postgres psql -c \"CREATE DATABASE linkshortener OWNER linkshortener;\"\n```\n\n**Step 2 — Run server-setup.sh** (from local machine):\n```bash\nscp -r deploy/ user@server:/tmp/ls-setup/\nssh user@server \"cd /tmp/ls-setup && bash server-setup.sh\"\n```\n\n**Step 3 — Fill in environment file** (on server):\n```bash\nssh user@server \"sudo nano /etc/linkshortener/environment\"\n# Fill: DATABASE_URL, JWT_SECRET, SESSION_SECRET, OAuth credentials, APP_BASE_URL, SUPER_ADMIN_EMAIL\n```\n\n**Step 4 — Apply DB schema** (from local machine):\n```bash\ncat sql/schema.sql | ssh user@server \"sudo -u postgres psql linkshortener\"\n```\n\n**Step 5 — Install Caddyfile + reload** (from local machine — edit domain first):\n```bash\n# Edit deploy/Caddyfile: replace \"your.domain.com\" with actual domain\nscp deploy/Caddyfile user@server:/tmp/Caddyfile\nssh user@server \"sudo cp /tmp/Caddyfile /etc/caddy/Caddyfile && sudo systemctl reload caddy\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Repeatable deployment (1 command)\n```bash\nmake deploy SSH_HOST=user@server APP_BASE_URL=https://yourdomain.com\n```\nBuilds backend binary + Vite frontend, rsyncs both to server, restarts the service.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n1. `ssh user@server \"sudo systemctl status linkshortener\"` — service active\n2. `curl -I https://yourdomain.com` — 200, TLS cert present\n3. `curl -I https://yourdomain.com/r/nonexistent` — 404 from backend (not Caddy 404)\n4. Open `https://yourdomain.com` in browser — Vue SPA loads, sign-in works\n\n---\n\n## Decisions\n- Build on local dev machine (linux/amd64 → server linux/amd64)\n- No Docker in production (Postgres + Caddy already on host)\n- No zero-downtime for now (brief systemctl restart pause)\n- `bin/` added to `.gitignore`\n- `environment.template` committed (no secrets), actual `/etc/linkshortener/environment` only on server\n- Subsequent schema migrations: apply individual `sql/00N_*.sql` files manually or via a future `migrate-prod` target\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_016Ph2qmvxfHyRRyBTBk7GFv__vscode-1773839707484","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

